  "text": "We observed an association between pubertal stage and obesity only on the univariable level. The direction of the relationship between weight status and the onset of puberty remains unclear. It has been suggested that obesity can cause an earlier onset of puberty, at least among girls [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . One explanation is that leptin provides the link between body fat and the onset of puberty by affecting gonadotropin secretion [CITATION_3] .",
